com.colofabrix.mathparser.expression

Class CmplxExpression

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.colofabrix.mathparser.expression.ExpressionEntry
      • com.colofabrix.mathparser.expression.CmplxExpression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<ExpressionEntry>, java.util.Collection<ExpressionEntry>, java.util.List<ExpressionEntry>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CmplxExpressionTest

    public class CmplxExpression
extends ExpressionEntry
implements java.util.List<ExpressionEntry>
    A composite expression represents an expression that is made by sub entries

    An example of composite expression is "1 + 2", which is made by two Operands and one Operator.

    Author:
    Fabrizio Colonna

      • fromExpression

        public static CmplxExpression fromExpression(java.lang.String expression,
                             Operators operators,
                             Memory memory)
                                      throws ExpressionException
        Creates a CmplxExpression starting from a string

        The method splits the string in its component and create an appropriate ExpressionEntry for every token.

        Parameters:
        expression - The expression to converts
        operators - A reference to the operators in use
        memory - A reference to the memory in use
        Returns:
        A CmplxExpression object containing the translated string expression
        Throws:
        ExpressionException

      • fromExpression

        public static CmplxExpression fromExpression(java.util.List<ExpressionEntry> stack,
                             Operators operators,
                             Memory memory)
                                      throws ExpressionException
        Creates a CmplxExpression starting from a string

        The method splits the string in its component and create an appropriate ExpressionEntry for every token.

        Parameters:
        stack - A stack of ExpressionEntry to add in a new CmplxExpression
        operators - A reference to the operators in use
        memory - A reference to the memory in use
        Returns:
        A CmplxExpression object containing the added CmplxExpression(s)
        Throws:
        ExpressionException
